This paper deals with topological data analysis, which is a subfield of computer science that involves the analysis of datasets using topological methods. The paper specifically focuses on the Mapper algorithm, which is commonly used in this field. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of persistence diagrams, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper presents algorithms for computing the multiscale mapper, which involves numerical computations, suggesting that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also a possible category.
